Minister of Finance Tito Mboweni. (Photo: Leila Dougan) “The IMF has released a basic Q&A on the kinds of facilities which are available at IMF,” Mboweni said. “We are not looking for budget support, we would be looking for the COVID-19 specific packages that we can access, and we are talking to them about that.” “We are looking at programmes which would not be accompanied by any structural adjustment programme,” he said. “We know what to do, we know what our structural reform programme is. We will not be looking into that at all.” (Reporting by Alexander Winning; writing by Olivia Kumwenda-Mtambo; Editing by Jon Boyle) Please note you must be a Maverick Insider to comment. Sign up here or sign in if you are already an Insider.